nd processes. Ideal PFR has uniform residence time; CSTR has broad RTD. Most real processes have RTDs between these extremes. | Tracer properties such as bulk density, flow function coefficient, and basic flow energy significantly impact RTD results. Tracer should be non-reactive, have physical properties similar to bulk material, be easily detectable, and not adhere to system surfaces. | Tracer selection significantly affects RTD measurements. Excess tracer can alter convection and diffusion phenomena. Tracer amount should be minimal to avoid disturbing bulk flow behavior. | Tracer mass should be below 5% of steady state mass hold-up in pulse tests. Step inputs in the range of 3-5% are sufficient for RTD determination. On-line techniques like NIR and UV spectrometry are preferred for real-time data acquisition. | Ideal reactor models (PFR, CSTR, laminar flow reactor) and non-ideal models (TIS) are used to characterize RTD. The Dirac delta function represents ideal PFR RTD. The exponential decay function represents ideal CSTR RTD. Laminar flow reactors have a parabolic velocity profile. The TIS model is used for non-ideal flow behavior.", "provenance": [{"document_id": "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing", "chunk_ids": ["2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_0_0", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_1_1", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_2_2", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_2_3", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_2_4", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_2_5", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_2_6", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_3_7", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_3_8", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_3_9", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_4_10", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_4_11", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_4_12", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_4_13", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_4_14", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_5_15", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_5_16", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_5_17", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_5_18", "2025_j_pharm_inv_-_understanding_and_development_of_residence_time_distribution_(rtd)_model_in_continuous_manufacturing_chunk_5_19", "2025