 23325.3, 26509.6, 25847.25, 15612.04, 13529.08, 14099.55, 14183.52, 3260.04, 57664.46, 13863.83, 13891.57], "unit": "s^2"}}, "tracer_experiment": {"tracer": null, "injection_method": "step tracer method", "detection_method": "monitoring the mass fraction of the tracer at the outlet", "detection_location": "reactor outlet"}, "flow_model": {"type": "simplified viscosity model", "parameters": {"viscosity_evolution": "based on mean age of fluid"}, "boundary_conditions": null}, "parameter_correlations": [], "key_findings": "Variable-viscosity fluid shows different flow behaviors such as dead zones and short-circuiting. Increasing impeller speed and extending space time can enhance mixing efficiency. Improved mixing in the second stage of the two-tank configuration eliminated concentration fluctuations caused by recirculating flow in the first tank, resulting in more uniform RTD curves. | Axial flow impeller is more likely to cause feed short circuit (>10% of the flow rate). | Axial flow impellers are more likely to cause feed short circuit (>10% of the flow rate). The disc structure of radial flow impellers suppresses short circuit. When the ratio of residence time to mixing time is less than 10, the dead zone volume increases significantly. Increasing impeller speed improves mixing but benefits diminish beyond ~375 rpm. | Increasing impeller speed improves mixing and approximates ideal behavior up to a threshold (375 rpm), beyond which benefits diminish and energy consumption rises sharply. Agitation reduces RTD tail and increases minimum residence time. Increasing fluid flow rate decreases mean residence time and deteriorates mixing performance. Higher fluid viscosity reduces back-mixing and prolongs residence time. When impeller discharge flow rate to feed rate ratio exceeds 13.13, reactor behavior resembles an ideal CSTR. Most RTD studies focus on turbulent flow regimes, with less exploration under laminar conditions. | Mixing characteristics depend on inlet and outlet spatial configuration. RTD behavior under laminar conditions is less explored. Fluid age distribution is an important parameter for evaluating mixing performance. Mean age contour maps can identify shortcircuiting and poorly mixed regions. RTD and fluid age distributions are consistent under laminar flow in a 2D tubular reactor.", "provenance": [{"document_id": "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity_", "chunk_ids": ["2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_1_1", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_2_2", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_3_3", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_3_4", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_3_5", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_3_6", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_3_7", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_4_8", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_5_9", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_5_10", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_6_11", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_6_13", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_6_14", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_7_15", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_8_16", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_8_17", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_8_18", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_8_19", "2025_processes_-_residence_time_distribution_of_variable_viscosity__chunk_8_20"